Next, we compared the epiallele composition between diagnosis (D) and relapse (R) stages for six AML patients (Additional file 1: Table S1). The epiallele composition and percentages were calculated for each covered locus, comparing the D vs. R status within each patient separately (Figure 3). All patients’ cells were processed at the same facility with the same purification methods (Ficoll gradient separation of mononuclear cells followed by lymphocyte depletion using CD3 and CD19 Miltenyi bead negative selection). Using the combinatorial entropy (as defined above), we examined the epiallele composition at each locus. The combinatorial entropy ranges from 0 to -144. The lower the combinatorial entropy, the larger the difference in epiallele composition between stages.Figure 3

